title: Album Page, "Sketches of Wooden Arches, Honfleur", June 7, 1887
medium: Graphite on blue paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, upper right corner: 20; lower right corner: 19; clockwise from bottom left drawing: arch of wood; section of bracket / for supporting overhang; Honfleur / June 7th 1887.
description: Vertical rectangle containing three sketches: above, a half-timbered building partially supported by a rusticated stone arch is seen at an angle.  The timbering is laid in intricate intersecting patterns, all unique. Below this at left and right are two different types of wood-supported spans.  The one at the right is a very straightforward bracket consisting of two pieces of wood intersecting at a 90-degree angle; the one at left is a detail of the arch in the sketch above.

tombstone.epitaph: Album Page, "Sketches of Wooden Arches, Honfleur", June 7, 1887.Graphite on blue paperboard tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-192.
